With the upcoming launch of the ecobee by Generac Smart Thermostat, a Load Managers category has been added to PowerPlay's Generac Catalog. In tandem with this category's introduction, all existing load manager items can now be found under the Load Managers category.

Because load manager items fell under the Accessories category previously, this transition will effectively remove any markups or view preferences your company set for the items impacted (listed below).

To ensure all Load Manager items are configured appropriately within any working proposals or Catalog Kits you may have them included in, we'd recommend reviewing and adjusting these items appropriately by navigating to Settings > MENU > Generac Catalog > Load Managers.

Impacted devices:

Generac Load Manager 50 Amp

Generac Load Manager 100 Amp

Generac HVAC Energy Manager

As new load management devices become available to purchase through Generac, you can expect to find them within the Load Managers category in PowerPlay moving forward.

If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to the PowerPlay team directly via email ( powerplay@generac.com) or phone at 888-436-3722 x 5678

Dear Valued PowerPlay Dealer,

With the changes communicated in Tuesday's email below, the following outlines additional information on how existing unclosed opportunities in the Powerplay database will be affected.

Please contact your dedicated Generac sales representative with questions.

New Opportunities as of 2/5/2024
Per Tuesday's communication below, the free warranty upgrade given to consumers that schedule an in-home consultation through the Generac Consumer Sales team will change to a FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY effective 2/5/2024.

Warranty Terms & Conditions
Generac is updating the Terms & Conditions for this offer to include a 90-day expiration date from the date the consumer contacts Generac either via a website form fill or phone call. These will be updated on Generac.com and made available in the Dealer 360 Document Library.

Existing Opportunities
Unclosed opportunities scheduled prior to 10/31/2023 will be changed to the FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY on 2/5/2024

Unclosed opportunities scheduled in the last 90 days (10/31/2023 2/4/2024) will remain eligible for the FREE 7-YEAR WARRANTY until EOD 5/5/2024. If these opportunities have not moved to Contract Signed status by EOD 5/5/2024, they will be changed to the FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY automatically.

Opportunities from FrontPage (Dealer customizable website through Marketing On Demand)
For dealers enrolled in FrontPage with PowerPlay connected, form fills completed through 2/4/2024 receive the FREE 7-YEAR WARRANTY. If these opportunities have not moved to Contract Signed status by EOD 5/5/2024, they will be change to the FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY automatically.

Please contact your dedicated Generac sales representative with questions

Dear Valued PowerPlay Dealer,

We are writing to inform you of updates to our Home Standby warranty offers given to consumers through Generac's National Campaigns and other Generac promotions such as the upcoming National Promotion.

National Campaign Warranty Promotion
Effective 2/5/24, the free warranty upgrade given to consumers that schedule an in-home consultation through the Generac Consumer Sales team and passed to dealers through PowerPlay will change to a FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY ($535 US/ $715 CAN value).

2024 Spring National Promotion
Generac is pleased to announce our next National Promotion!

  • Promotion dates: April 1, 2024 May 12, 2024
  • Offer: Free 7-Year Extended Warranty - $735 US / $945 CAN Value
  • Install deadline: July 21, 2024
  • Details and customizable marketing assets coming soon!

Generacs national advertising and marketing efforts continue to drive a sense of urgency for consumers to purchase. This change to the warranty promotion strategy enables installers to upsell the consumer to a 10-year warranty and drive more revenue to their bottom-line while offering an effective closing tool.

For full details on Generac extended warranty options, view Generacs Extended Warranty Brochure. Generac also offers a complimentary training on Generac University. Click here to register, and if you do not already have a log-in for Generac University please follow these instructions for account set up.

Upgradable Warranty Opportunities*
Warranty Promotion Warranty Upgrades Available (Stackable)
IHC scheduled through Generac 5yr C 5yr Extended
April-May 2024 National Promotion 7yr C 3yr Extended

*Note: The Mobile Link Connectivity 5yr Upgrade warranty does not qualify for any stackable warranty coverage.

As always, we appreciate your continued alliance.

","startDate":"2024-01-16T01:53:18.68","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2024-01-16T01:53:18.68","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":28,"title":"December 5th, 2023 Auto Rejection Feature","message":"

As of 12/5/23, PowerPlay will turn on an auto rejection feature. This feature will automatically remove any opportunity with a 'Scheduled by Generac' or Warm Transfer Accept status that has been in your account for longer than 48 cumulative hours (excluding weekends). Opportunities that expire will then be reassigned to a different dealer for In-Home Consultation purposes.

Prior to this change, we encourage you to update all opportunities that are currently in either a 'Scheduled by Generac' or 'Warm Transfer Accept' status by 12/5/23, or you will lose visibility to those consumers in PowerPlay.

How do I know when an opportunity will expire?

  • Your PowerPlay Dashboard will display any opportunities in the 'Scheduled by Generac' or 'Warm Transfer Accept' status, and each will have an expiration count-down timer displayed.

Prior to the expiration timer running out, you are required to take one of the following actions:

  • Accept the opportunity
    • Click Next Steps to confirm or reschedule the assessment date with the consumer
  • Decline the opportunity and select a decline option, leaving notes if applicable

NOTE: You can view the full consumer details within the Opportunities area of PowerPlay before accepting or declining the opportunity.

","startDate":"2023-11-17T19:48:19.4766667","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-11-17T19:48:19.4766667","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":27,"title":"November 7th, 2023 Digital Signature","message":"

We are excited to announce PowerPlays inclusion of a digital signature feature! After selecting a proposal from the Review and Approve area of a customers opportunity, selecting the Customer Link button will present the option to copy a unique link for the proposal. Once copied, the link can be sent to the customer via email and/or text.

Digital Signature Troubleshooting Tips

  • The Customer Link button is available for 30 days after a proposal has been generated. If a proposal was generated longer than 30 days ago, a new proposal will need to be generated to utilize the Customer Link option.
  • While copy and paste is supported on iOS versions 13.4.1 and higher, as future iOS updates become available, highlighting the text to copy the customer link may be required on certain devices (we will do our best to ensure that this functionality is successful on current iOS versions).
  • Reviewing and signing off on proposals that have been digitally signed by a customer can only be accomplished by PowerPlay users set up as an Admin and/or Sales Rep This functionality is not available or visible for Call Agents

If a customer is experiencing any issues with a proposal link:

  • Confirm their device has internet access
  • Generate and send a new proposal link
  • If necessary, dealers may contact PowerPlay for additional troubleshooting/assistance

Please refrain from providing customers with the PowerPlay teams extension

Please Note: This new method of obtaining a customers signature will not replace any current functionality in PowerPlay. In addition to the Sign Now option for PowerPlay proposals remaining available, you are in no way required to use the digital signature feature moving forward

As of August 1st, the Sales > PowerPlay > Dealer Library and Installation Checklist areas of Dealer Connection will no longer be accessible.

After August 1st, any updates or changes to the Dealer Library or Installation Checklist area will need to be made by logging into the PowerPlay website and navigating to Settings > Sales Settings > Dealer Library/Installation Checklist.

Upon the conclusion of this final transition, all of your accounts PowerPlay settings will be accessible exclusively through the Settings > Sales Settings area of your PowerPlay portal.

We will keep you as informed as possible of all upcoming changes as timelines and updates become available. Please feel free to reach out to the PowerPlay team directly with any questions or concerns.

","startDate":"2023-04-06T20:28:38.8066667","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-04-06T20:28:38.8066667","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":16,"title":"PowerPlay Training Update","message":"

We are excited to announce that all PowerPlay training content is now available through the Generac University. All live and on-demand webinars for PowerPlay can be accessed by navigating to Generac University (https://generac-fs.inquisiqlms.com) or through Dealer 360 > Training > Generac University.

To access all PowerPlay training webinars, you will first need to complete the PowerPlay Training Enrollment Request course, which can be found by logging into the Generac University and navigating to Catalog > Sales Training > PowerPlay. Completing this preliminary course requires uploading the E invoice your company received upon purchasing a PowerPlay subscription.

Once an invoice has been uploaded and our team has verified your information, youll receive confirmation via email and be granted access to enroll in all live and on-demand training webinars.

If you have not been set up with credentials for the Generac University website or are unable to log in, please send an email to servicetraining@generac.com or contact the Service Learning Center team at 888-436-3722 ext. 4172 for assistance.

New Features

PowerPlay

  • The scheduled appointments area is now available as a calendar view able to be viewed at a month, week and day glance
  • Simplified source filtering including the ability to view source when opportunities are exported via an excel file
  • Character count added to the placement walkthrough, quote, diagram, and customer information note areas

","startDate":"2023-02-17T23:16:14.9566667","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-02-17T23:16:14.9566667","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":14,"title":"Install and Service Program","message":"Hello PowerPlay Partner,

Were excited to announce an update to our PowerPlay platform for those dealers that are currently selling generators under the Install & Service program, powered by the Advantage Alliance.

The Install & Service program combines a lease of a generator, annual maintenance, Mobile LinkTM and comprehensive warranty for a set monthly fee to the consumer over 10 years. For those dealers that are interested in the program or would like more information, be sure to visit the Advantage Alliance booth at next weeks dealer conference or email the team at info@advantageallianceprogram.com

Shortly after you are enrolled and have taken training, you will be able to select Advantage Leasing as an option in PowerPlay quotes under the options tab within the quote builder page. When an option is selected you will see the quote summary update to display the monthly payment which can then be added to a proposal along with the auto populated Terms and Conditions of the Advantage Program.

* This program and PowerPlay feature are only available to dealers that have completed Level 1 training (introduction to the program, benefits, processes, etc.).

As always, thank you for your continued partnership.

Sincerely,
The Generac Team","startDate":"2023-01-12T02:36:34.1","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-01-12T02:36:34.1","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":13,"title":"PowerPlay Catalog Updates: Price Adjustment Options","message":"Dear Valued PowerPlay Partner,

We wanted to inform you of an upcoming change to the PowerPlay catalog that will occur the weekend of 12/17/22. To remain consistent with the pricing you see when purchasing product through Dealer Connection or Dealer 360, all items in the Generac Catalog Items area of your account will soon reflect their MSRP values instead of your Dealer Price. In addition to the modified view, the options available to adjust your pricing will also be updated.

When this change occurs, your PowerPlay pricing will NOT be immediately impacted. Instead, the price modifier for each Generac item will be adjusted to the appropriate markup amount to keep the Customer Price at whatever value you have established. This will allow you to continue generating PowerPlay proposals with the appropriate pricing while you become acclimated with the changes.

Updated Price Adjustment Options:

For both options, entering a positive value will increase the Customer Price, and entering a negative value will decrease it.

When the Dollar Amount option is selected:
Customer Price = MSRP +/- value entered

When the Percentage option is selected:
Customer Price = MSRP +/- (MSRP value entered)

Examples: MSRP = $100, Percentage option selected and a value of 10 is entered.
The Customer Price ($100 + 100 X 10%) would equal $110

MSRP = $100, Percentage option selected and a value of -10 is entered.
The Customer Price ($100 - 100 X 10%) would equal $90

If you have any questions, please dont hesitate to reach out to the PowerPlay team directly.

Sincerely,

The PowerPlay Team

With the upcoming launch of the ecobee by Generac Smart Thermostat, a Load Managers category has been added to PowerPlay's Generac Catalog. In tandem with this category's introduction, all existing load manager items can now be found under the Load Managers category.

Because load manager items fell under the Accessories category previously, this transition will effectively remove any markups or view preferences your company set for the items impacted (listed below).

To ensure all Load Manager items are configured appropriately within any working proposals or Catalog Kits you may have them included in, we'd recommend reviewing and adjusting these items appropriately by navigating to Settings > MENU > Generac Catalog > Load Managers.

Impacted devices:

Generac Load Manager 50 Amp

Generac Load Manager 100 Amp

Generac HVAC Energy Manager

As new load management devices become available to purchase through Generac, you can expect to find them within the Load Managers category in PowerPlay moving forward.

If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to the PowerPlay team directly via email ( powerplay@generac.com) or phone at 888-436-3722 x 5678

Dear Valued PowerPlay Dealer,

With the changes communicated in Tuesday's email below, the following outlines additional information on how existing unclosed opportunities in the Powerplay database will be affected.

Please contact your dedicated Generac sales representative with questions.

New Opportunities as of 2/5/2024
Per Tuesday's communication below, the free warranty upgrade given to consumers that schedule an in-home consultation through the Generac Consumer Sales team will change to a FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY effective 2/5/2024.

Warranty Terms & Conditions
Generac is updating the Terms & Conditions for this offer to include a 90-day expiration date from the date the consumer contacts Generac either via a website form fill or phone call. These will be updated on Generac.com and made available in the Dealer 360 Document Library.

Existing Opportunities
Unclosed opportunities scheduled prior to 10/31/2023 will be changed to the FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY on 2/5/2024

Unclosed opportunities scheduled in the last 90 days (10/31/2023 2/4/2024) will remain eligible for the FREE 7-YEAR WARRANTY until EOD 5/5/2024. If these opportunities have not moved to Contract Signed status by EOD 5/5/2024, they will be changed to the FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY automatically.

Opportunities from FrontPage (Dealer customizable website through Marketing On Demand)
For dealers enrolled in FrontPage with PowerPlay connected, form fills completed through 2/4/2024 receive the FREE 7-YEAR WARRANTY. If these opportunities have not moved to Contract Signed status by EOD 5/5/2024, they will be change to the FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY automatically.

Please contact your dedicated Generac sales representative with questions

Dear Valued PowerPlay Dealer,

We are writing to inform you of updates to our Home Standby warranty offers given to consumers through Generac's National Campaigns and other Generac promotions such as the upcoming National Promotion.

National Campaign Warranty Promotion
Effective 2/5/24, the free warranty upgrade given to consumers that schedule an in-home consultation through the Generac Consumer Sales team and passed to dealers through PowerPlay will change to a FREE 5-YEAR WARRANTY ($535 US/ $715 CAN value).

2024 Spring National Promotion
Generac is pleased to announce our next National Promotion!

  • Promotion dates: April 1, 2024 May 12, 2024
  • Offer: Free 7-Year Extended Warranty - $735 US / $945 CAN Value
  • Install deadline: July 21, 2024
  • Details and customizable marketing assets coming soon!

Generacs national advertising and marketing efforts continue to drive a sense of urgency for consumers to purchase. This change to the warranty promotion strategy enables installers to upsell the consumer to a 10-year warranty and drive more revenue to their bottom-line while offering an effective closing tool.

For full details on Generac extended warranty options, view Generacs Extended Warranty Brochure. Generac also offers a complimentary training on Generac University. Click here to register, and if you do not already have a log-in for Generac University please follow these instructions for account set up.

Upgradable Warranty Opportunities*
Warranty Promotion Warranty Upgrades Available (Stackable)
IHC scheduled through Generac 5yr C 5yr Extended
April-May 2024 National Promotion 7yr C 3yr Extended

*Note: The Mobile Link Connectivity 5yr Upgrade warranty does not qualify for any stackable warranty coverage.

As always, we appreciate your continued alliance.

","startDate":"2024-01-16T01:53:18.68","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2024-01-16T01:53:18.68","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":28,"title":"December 5th, 2023 Auto Rejection Feature","message":"

As of 12/5/23, PowerPlay will turn on an auto rejection feature. This feature will automatically remove any opportunity with a 'Scheduled by Generac' or Warm Transfer Accept status that has been in your account for longer than 48 cumulative hours (excluding weekends). Opportunities that expire will then be reassigned to a different dealer for In-Home Consultation purposes.

Prior to this change, we encourage you to update all opportunities that are currently in either a 'Scheduled by Generac' or 'Warm Transfer Accept' status by 12/5/23, or you will lose visibility to those consumers in PowerPlay.

How do I know when an opportunity will expire?

  • Your PowerPlay Dashboard will display any opportunities in the 'Scheduled by Generac' or 'Warm Transfer Accept' status, and each will have an expiration count-down timer displayed.

Prior to the expiration timer running out, you are required to take one of the following actions:

  • Accept the opportunity
    • Click Next Steps to confirm or reschedule the assessment date with the consumer
  • Decline the opportunity and select a decline option, leaving notes if applicable

NOTE: You can view the full consumer details within the Opportunities area of PowerPlay before accepting or declining the opportunity.

","startDate":"2023-11-17T19:48:19.4766667","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-11-17T19:48:19.4766667","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":27,"title":"November 7th, 2023 Digital Signature","message":"

We are excited to announce PowerPlays inclusion of a digital signature feature! After selecting a proposal from the Review and Approve area of a customers opportunity, selecting the Customer Link button will present the option to copy a unique link for the proposal. Once copied, the link can be sent to the customer via email and/or text.

Digital Signature Troubleshooting Tips

  • The Customer Link button is available for 30 days after a proposal has been generated. If a proposal was generated longer than 30 days ago, a new proposal will need to be generated to utilize the Customer Link option.
  • While copy and paste is supported on iOS versions 13.4.1 and higher, as future iOS updates become available, highlighting the text to copy the customer link may be required on certain devices (we will do our best to ensure that this functionality is successful on current iOS versions).
  • Reviewing and signing off on proposals that have been digitally signed by a customer can only be accomplished by PowerPlay users set up as an Admin and/or Sales Rep This functionality is not available or visible for Call Agents

If a customer is experiencing any issues with a proposal link:

  • Confirm their device has internet access
  • Generate and send a new proposal link
  • If necessary, dealers may contact PowerPlay for additional troubleshooting/assistance

Please refrain from providing customers with the PowerPlay teams extension

Please Note: This new method of obtaining a customers signature will not replace any current functionality in PowerPlay. In addition to the Sign Now option for PowerPlay proposals remaining available, you are in no way required to use the digital signature feature moving forward

As of August 1st, the Sales > PowerPlay > Dealer Library and Installation Checklist areas of Dealer Connection will no longer be accessible.

After August 1st, any updates or changes to the Dealer Library or Installation Checklist area will need to be made by logging into the PowerPlay website and navigating to Settings > Sales Settings > Dealer Library/Installation Checklist.

Please Note: The Sales Settings area of PowerPlay referenced above is only accessible to users who have the Admin and/or Sales Rep role enabled.

Upon the conclusion of this final transition, all of your accounts PowerPlay settings will be accessible exclusively through the Settings > Sales Settings area of your PowerPlay portal.

We will keep you as informed as possible of all upcoming changes as timelines and updates become available. Please feel free to reach out to the PowerPlay team directly with any questions or concerns.

","startDate":"2023-04-06T20:28:38.8066667","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-04-06T20:28:38.8066667","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":16,"title":"PowerPlay Training Update","message":"

We are excited to announce that all PowerPlay training content is now available through the Generac University. All live and on-demand webinars for PowerPlay can be accessed by navigating to Generac University (https://generac-fs.inquisiqlms.com) or through Dealer 360 > Training > Generac University.

To access all PowerPlay training webinars, you will first need to complete the PowerPlay Training Enrollment Request course, which can be found by logging into the Generac University and navigating to Catalog > Sales Training > PowerPlay. Completing this preliminary course requires uploading the E invoice your company received upon purchasing a PowerPlay subscription.

Once an invoice has been uploaded and our team has verified your information, youll receive confirmation via email and be granted access to enroll in all live and on-demand training webinars.

If you have not been set up with credentials for the Generac University website or are unable to log in, please send an email to servicetraining@generac.com or contact the Service Learning Center team at 888-436-3722 ext. 4172 for assistance.

PowerPlay

","startDate":"2023-02-17T23:16:14.9566667","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-02-17T23:16:14.9566667","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":14,"title":"Install and Service Program","message":"Hello PowerPlay Partner,

Were excited to announce an update to our PowerPlay platform for those dealers that are currently selling generators under the Install & Service program, powered by the Advantage Alliance.

The Install & Service program combines a lease of a generator, annual maintenance, Mobile LinkTM and comprehensive warranty for a set monthly fee to the consumer over 10 years. For those dealers that are interested in the program or would like more information, be sure to visit the Advantage Alliance booth at next weeks dealer conference or email the team at info@advantageallianceprogram.com

Shortly after you are enrolled and have taken training, you will be able to select Advantage Leasing as an option in PowerPlay quotes under the options tab within the quote builder page. When an option is selected you will see the quote summary update to display the monthly payment which can then be added to a proposal along with the auto populated Terms and Conditions of the Advantage Program.

* This program and PowerPlay feature are only available to dealers that have completed Level 1 training (introduction to the program, benefits, processes, etc.).

As always, thank you for your continued partnership.

Sincerely,
The Generac Team","startDate":"2023-01-12T02:36:34.1","endDate":"9999-12-31T23:59:59.9999999","createdDate":"2023-01-12T02:36:34.1","createdBy":null,"modifiedDateTime":null,"modifiedBy":null},{"id":13,"title":"PowerPlay Catalog Updates: Price Adjustment Options","message":"Dear Valued PowerPlay Partner,

We wanted to inform you of an upcoming change to the PowerPlay catalog that will occur the weekend of 12/17/22. To remain consistent with the pricing you see when purchasing product through Dealer Connection or Dealer 360, all items in the Generac Catalog Items area of your account will soon reflect their MSRP values instead of your Dealer Price. In addition to the modified view, the options available to adjust your pricing will also be updated.

When this change occurs, your PowerPlay pricing will NOT be immediately impacted. Instead, the price modifier for each Generac item will be adjusted to the appropriate markup amount to keep the Customer Price at whatever value you have established. This will allow you to continue generating PowerPlay proposals with the appropriate pricing while you become acclimated with the changes.

Updated Price Adjustment Options:

For both options, entering a positive value will increase the Customer Price, and entering a negative value will decrease it.

When the Dollar Amount option is selected:
Customer Price = MSRP +/- value entered

When the Percentage option is selected:
Customer Price = MSRP +/- (MSRP value entered)

Examples: MSRP = $100, Percentage option selected and a value of 10 is entered.
The Customer Price ($100 + 100 X 10%) would equal $110

MSRP = $100, Percentage option selected and a value of -10 is entered.
The Customer Price ($100 - 100 X 10%) would equal $90

If you have any questions, please dont hesitate to reach out to the PowerPlay team directly.

Sincerely,

The PowerPlay Team
